# Agent Room Case - Title Settings Entry Brainstorm

## Case

- Date: 2026-06-03
- Case name: title_settings_entry_brainstorm_2026-06-03
- User request: 타이틀 화면에 설정 화면 진입점을 만들 예정이며, 어떤 설정 사항들이 필요한지 기획 에이전트 3명 정도로 논의 시작
- Executor decision: Use Agent Room routing before subagents. Primary methodology is Superpowers brainstorming. No implementation in this phase.

## Method Route

- Primary methodology: Superpowers brainstorming
- Supporting methodology: project_develop_policy.md, Planner existing title-screen records, Agent Room routing
- Project policy checked: yes
- Implementation status: implemented on 2026-06-04

## Selected Agents

### product-manager

- Role: define MVP scope, first-screen priority, commute-time user value
- Main viewpoint: settings must not weaken fast game start from title
- Authority: read-only discussion
- Output target: Planner/Essential_game_plan/ synthesis by parent Codex

### ui-designer

- Role: define title settings entry location, modal/screen structure, interaction states, mobile readability
- Main viewpoint: 9:16 portrait, one-thumb interaction, low visual clutter
- Authority: read-only discussion
- Output target: Planner/Essential_game_plan/ synthesis by parent Codex

### game-developer

- Role: evaluate implementation realism for persisted settings, runtime effects, state transitions, and current code fit
- Main viewpoint: avoid expensive settings that require unfinished audio/graphics/control systems
- Authority: read-only discussion
- Output target: Developer/ technical notes if implementation planning starts

## Required Output Folders

- Routing record: Developer/agent_room/
- Planning synthesis: Planner/Essential_game_plan/
- Graphics record: Graphic_designer/ only if visual concept expands beyond entry placement and interaction
- QA record: Quaility_Assurance/ only after implementation or validation planning

## Verification Gate

- Discussion phase completed before implementation.
- Existing title-screen purpose remains intact: fast first game start.
- MVP settings and later settings are separated.
- The setting entry point does not reintroduce coin shop or other non-MVP title actions.
- User approved implementation with top-right gear entry and floating modal.

## Implementation Result

- Entry point: top-right gear button on `Developer/r3f_prototype/src/components/TitleScreen.jsx`
- Modal style: compact floating popup over the title screen
- MVP settings implemented: vibration toggle, reduced-effects toggle, controls help panel
- Persistence: `localStorage` key `school_survivor:titleSettings`
- Regression coverage: `Developer/r3f_prototype/src/components/TitleScreen.settings.test.jsx`

## Do-Not-Skip Rules

- Do not bypass Superpowers brainstorming.
- Do not let subagents replace project policy or write implementation code.
- Do not add title-screen complexity that competes with the primary start action.
- Do not create graphics/3D implementation work from planning text alone.
